item.description:
While this article is mainly about how to manually test Java family Paketo buildpacks, still, most of the instructions should work fine with other Paketo buildpacks; and even non Paketo buildpacks!
Suppose that you started working on a new feature for the spring-boot buildpack&hellip;
Unit tests first Of course, during your development, you will make sure that you did not break any tests, regularly running go test -v ./... but you would also add new tests covering your new code; the classic combination go test -v .
